The paper discusses peer-assessment experiments conducted in computer science courses, which suggests that it belongs to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The datasets are designed to be used in a variety of experiments, including performance prediction and text similarity tasks, which further supports the inclusion of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions that the datasets are reported as parsable data structures, which could be useful in Computer Engineering (cs.CE) applications.
